reviews.review: It was great! All around well done. I was hoping to see baby Yoda. However maybe in films to come. I'm sure we don't want to take away from Mandalorian just yet. Special Thanks to Disney for keeping on point. So surprised and happy to see Leia in this film for her last performance. Excellent! May the Force be with you all. Be well...
perfect ending to the 42 year long saga.
Awesome movie with an unexpected twist for an ending.
Great finish.  I don’t know why any Star Wars fan wouldn’t like this.

Never has a film been so cluelessly driven, the last three films of the series suffer from a lack of mapping that the first three filmed in the series didn't suffer as much from, and the second three filmed in the series  didn't suffer at all although at least this third three didn't suffer from Jar Jar Binks or the excessive, over mechanical CGI that made them so lacking in emotional connection.  A film in the series has not been so unworthy as Phantom Menace until the Rise of Skywalker.

The Mandalorian is a western re-imagined, and does a better job on the smaller screen.  Just like Solo missed the boat on the re-imagining of the swashbuckler, while Rogue One re-imagined the war trope and took it to a new level, this one misses the samurai trope by a mile and a half.

It now is  number 5, 4, 3, 8, 7,  6, 2, 9, and 1  a sub par ending to the Skywalker Saga when 7 was a rehash but well done, and 8 was reimagining that should have setup 9 for the ending to end all endings if only they had had the imagination on the one end and the clarity of thought to fulfill a proper samurai ending in the other.

Run away from this unworthy calamity.  If you want poor editing, rushed pacing, and unimaginative CGI combined with uncreative story telling go see it.  If you were hoping for an Akiro sweeping overview and Toshiro precipice driven angst and yet triumphant denouement then this is a disappointment of gargantuan proportions.

Thought that the flaws in the film were easily overlooked and there was a warm sense of closure with the film.  Good role models projected while maintaining the adventure and original characters that influenced our generation.  It still maintains the thrill of the overall franchise and leaves the future to the younger generations.
I was not great but it was better than I had thought it would be from the reviews I read.

Thank goodness Abrams returned to direct this one. It's a great ending to the saga. For me, there weren't any slow moments. The film just keeps you going. Wish there were more lightsaber battles, but I need to remember this isn't the prequels.
Loved it. I am not a Star Wars fan, my daughter wanted to go! But now, I am!!
